BuilderChannel
/ Builder channel sink. Goal-backed channel registered at Build start so all
/ build-time output flows through one named seam — later we can swap the consumer
/ (file log, TUI, structured stream) without touching the call sites.
/
/ The forwarding step (`- write out %!data%`) is removed: a goal-backed channel sets
/ %!data% in the actor context, but it isn't reaching the goal body here, so it printed
/ the literal "%!data%" instead of the message. Restore the forward once channel-input
/ propagation to a goal-backed channel is fixed (see todos).
